{"title_page": "Magaly Quintana", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{short description|Nicaraguan historian and Catholic feminist activist}}\n'''Magaly Quintana Pereyra''' (28 May 1952<ref>https://www.laprensa.com.ni/2017/10/22/suplemento/la-prensa-domingo/2318559-magaly-quintana-el-estado-invisibiliza-femicidios</ref> \u2013 5 May 2019) was a Nicaraguan feminist historian and activist.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news |last1=Cruz |first1=Eduardo |title=Fallece Magaly Quintana, abanderada de la lucha contra los femicidios |url=https://www.laprensa.com.ni/2019/05/05/nacionales/2547267-fallece-abanderada-de-la-lucha-contra-los-femicidios |accessdate=6 May 2019 |work=La Prensa |date=5 May 2019 |language=es}}</ref> She was director of Catholic Women for the Right to Choose, advocating for the right to [[therapeutic abortion]] following its ban in Nicaragua in 2006.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kalantari |first1=Shuka |title=Women in Nicaragua fight for the right to get abortions that could save their lives |url=https://www.pri.org/stories/2016-08-16/women-nicaragua-fight-right-get-abortions-could-save-their-lives |accessdate=6 May 2019 |work=Public Radio International |date=16 August 2016 |language=en}}</ref> She also led advocacy opposing violence against women, raising awareness of [[femicide]] in the country.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gonz\u00e1lez |first1=Mauricio |title=El Nuevo Diario |url=https://www.elnuevodiario.com.ni/nacionales/482529-femicidios-2018-maltrato-violencia-nicaragua/ |accessdate=6 May 2019 |work=El Nuevo Diario |date=3 January 2019 |language=es}}</ref> In 2018, she joined the [[2018-2019 Nicaraguan protests|anti-government protests]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://confidencial.com.ni/english-widespread-grief-at-the-death-of-magaly-quintana/|title=Widespread Grief at the Death of Magaly Quintana, fighter for Nicaraguan Women\u2019s Rights|last=Mungu\u00eda|first=Ivette|date=2019-05-06|website=Confidencial|access-date=2019-05-07}}</ref>\n\nQuintana was born 28 May 1952.<ref name=\":1\">{{cite news|url=https://www.laprensa.com.ni/2017/10/22/suplemento/la-prensa-domingo/2318559-magaly-quintana-el-estado-invisibiliza-femicidios|title=Magaly Quintana: \"El Estado invisibiliza femicidios\"|last1=Gonz\u00e1lez C.|first1=Alejandra|date=22 October 2017|work=La Prensa|accessdate=6 May 2019|language=es}}</ref> She attended [[Colegio La Asunci\u00f3n|La Asunci\u00f3n]] for high school, then entered university, becoming a student leader.<ref name=\":1\" /> She joined the [[Nicaraguan Revolution]], then in 1982 began working in feminist organizing.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nShe died of a stroke on 5 May 2019, aged 66.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Quintana, Magaly}}\n[[Category:Nicaraguan feminists]]\n[[Category:Nicaraguan historians]]\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:2019 deaths]]\n[[Category:Proponents of Christian feminism]]\n[[Category:Abortion-rights activists]]\n[[Category:Deaths from cerebrovascular disease]]\n[[Category:Nicaraguan revolutionaries]]\n[[Category:Women in war in Central America]]\n[[Category:Nicaraguan women in politics]]\n[[Category:People of the Nicaraguan Revolution]]\n[[Category:Women in warfare post-1945]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{short description|Nicaraguan historian and Catholic feminist activist}}\n'''Magaly Quintana Pereyra''' (28 May 1952<ref>https://www.laprensa.com.ni/2017/10/22/suplemento/la-prensa-domingo/2318559-magaly-quintana-el-estado-invisibiliza-femicidios</ref> \u2013 5 May 2019) was a Nicaraguan feminist historian and activist.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news |last1=Cruz |first1=Eduardo |title=Fallece Magaly Quintana, abanderada de la lucha contra los femicidios |url=https://www.laprensa.com.ni/2019/05/05/nacionales/2547267-fallece-abanderada-de-la-lucha-contra-los-femicidios |accessdate=6 May 2019 |work=La Prensa |date=5 May 2019 |language=es}}</ref> She was director of Catholic Women for the Right to Choose, advocating for the right to [[therapeutic abortion]] following its ban in Nicaragua in 2006.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kalantari |first1=Shuka |title=Women in Nicaragua fight for the right to get abortions that could save their lives |url=https://www.pri.org/stories/2016-08-16/women-nicaragua-fight-right-get-abortions-could-save-their-lives |accessdate=6 May 2019 |work=Public Radio International |date=16 August 2016 |language=en}}</ref> She also led advocacy opposing violence against women, raising awareness of [[femicide]] in the country.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gonz\u00e1lez |first1=Mauricio |title=El Nuevo Diario |url=https://www.elnuevodiario.com.ni/nacionales/482529-femicidios-2018-maltrato-violencia-nicaragua/ |accessdate=6 May 2019 |work=El Nuevo Diario |date=3 January 2019 |language=es}}</ref> In 2018, she joined the [[2018-2019 Nicaraguan protests|anti-government protests]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://confidencial.com.ni/english-widespread-grief-at-the-death-of-magaly-quintana/|title=Widespread Grief at the Death of Magaly Quintana, fighter for Nicaraguan Women\u2019s Rights|last=Mungu\u00eda|first=Ivette|date=2019-05-06|website=Confidencial|access-date=2019-05-07}}</ref>\n\nQuintana was born 28 May 1952.<ref name=\":1\">{{cite news|url=https://www.laprensa.com.ni/2017/10/22/suplemento/la-prensa-domingo/2318559-magaly-quintana-el-estado-invisibiliza-femicidios|title=Magaly Quintana: \"El Estado invisibiliza femicidios\"|last1=Gonz\u00e1lez C.|first1=Alejandra|date=22 October 2017|work=La Prensa|accessdate=6 May 2019|language=es}}</ref> She attended [[Colegio La Asunci\u00f3n|La Asunci\u00f3n]] for high school, then entered university, becoming a student leader.<ref name=\":1\" /> She joined the [[Nicaraguan Revolution]], then in 1982 began working in feminist organizing.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nShe died of a stroke on 5 May 2019, aged 66.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Quintana, Magaly}}\n[[Category:Nicaraguan feminists]]\n[[Category:Nicaraguan historians]]\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:2019 deaths]]\n[[Category:Proponents of Christian feminism]]\n[[Category:Abortion-rights activists]]\n[[Category:Deaths from cerebrovascular disease]]\n[[Category:Nicaraguan revolutionaries]]\n[[Category:Women in war in Central America]]\n[[Category:Nicaraguan women in politics]]\n[[Category:People of the Nicaraguan Revolution]]\n[[Category:Women in warfare post-1945]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magaly_Quintana"}
